criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Severe NS, defined as proteinuria exceeding 3.5 g/24h or 50 mg/kg/24h and serum
             albumin ≤2.5 g/dL;

          -  eGFR ≥30 mL/min/1.73 m2.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Body mass index (BMI) ≥40 kg/m2;

          -  Low body mass (<45 kg for female, <57 kg for male);

          -  Acute VTE;

          -  Previously introduced anticoagulation (due to comorbidities);

          -  Contraindications for enoxaparin;

          -  Pregnancy.
